      <p>Hmm&#8230; i don&#8217;t know why, but i&#8217;m sure you can find fish sauce that doesn&#8217;t contain msg. ours listed ingredients as Fermented Round Scad Fish Extract, Iodized Salt, Caramel and Potassium Sorbate(as preservative). It&#8217;s a local Philippine brand though and fish sace or &#8220;patis&#8221; as we call it, ranks up there with sugar cane vinegar as the dip and seasoning of choice.</></>add a squeeze of calamansi(philippine lemon) or lime, and it&#8217;s great served alongside fried fish.</></>Julie got it right&#8230;some chopped garlic and sugar, and it&#8217;s great with dumplings&#8230;or fried porkchops!</></>if people think fish sauce stinks&#8230; they should try shrimp paste! stinky, but yummy! especially with green mangoes!</p>
